25/08/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The IMF agrees with Serbian officials on the need to raise the budget deficit target from the original 3% of GDP, the government said on Monday (August 24th), following day one of talks with IMF officials, regarding the next 800m-euro instalment of the IMF loan. Talks move next to a technical discussion and determining the actual new target. After Monday's session, Labour Minister Rasim Ljajic said there will be no cuts in pensions, salaries or social spending. The IMF approved a 2.9 billion-euro stand-by arrangement with Serbia in mid-May. Belgrade has already drawn the first 788m-euro tranche. (Beta, Tanjug, RTS, B92 - 24/08/09)
